Fresh from winning the Barclays Premier League title Manchester City took their celebration party to the beach on Wednesday.

Manuel Pellegrini's side secured their second title in three years with a comfortable 2-0 win over West Ham on the final day of the season to finish two points clear of Liverpool.

Captain Vincent Kompany and his City team-mates turned Manchester blue on Monday during their open-top bus parade, and just 48 hours later were pictured hitting the beach in Abu Dhabi.

