It seems as though the tour will be a fitting end to an excellent season for City, after adding the Premier League to the Capital One Cup they won after beating Sunderland at Wembley in March.

And it is expected that England stars Joe Hart and James Milner - after being called into Roy Hodgson's World Cup squad on Monday afternoon - will not play a part in Thursday's exhibition match.

The Three Lions manager will be hoping both players will be fit ahead of their meeting up with the rest of the squad next Monday.

